President Joe Biden visited the East Portland Community Center in Portland, Oregon to discuss lower drug costs and healthcare affordability. He thanked Senator Ron Wyden for his leadership in passing significant legislation to address these issues. President Biden highlighted the high cost of prescription drugs in the United States compared to other countries and the need to hold pharmaceutical companies accountable. He emphasized the Inflation Reduction Act, which allows Medicare to negotiate lower drug prices and caps out-of-pocket costs for seniors. The President also mentioned the affordability of vaccines, hearing aids, and healthcare coverage under the Affordable Care Act. He warned against Republican efforts to repeal these measures and urged Americans to remember the importance of affordable healthcare and investments in education and infrastructure for the future of the country.